{
  "texts": [
    "This allows domain-adaptation of general-purpose language models.",
    "General-purpose LMs achieve high performance across many tasks (Sun et al. 2019), yet performance typically drops in out-of domain settings.",
    "Several studies explored further-pretraining on domain-specific data (Zhu et al. 2021), in such cases, demonstrating that further-pretraining even on small-sized task-specific data can improve results in out-of-domain down-stream tasks (Gururangan et al. 2020).",
    "PLMs for the medical domain.",
    "Medical PLMs, pretrained on medical data from scratch and further-pretrained medical PLMs, have outperformed general PLMs in several tasks (Sivarajkumar and Wang 2022; Taylor et al. 2023)."
  ]
}